import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split, GridSearchCV
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, roc_auc_score, confusion_matrix, classification_report, roc_curve, auc
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE

# 2. Load Dataset
df = pd.read_csv("Train.csv")
target = "Reached.on.Time_Y.N"

# 3. Handle Missing Values
df = df.dropna()

# 4. Outlier Treatment (IQR method)
numeric_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=['int64', 'float64']).columns
for col in numeric_cols:
    Q1 = df[col].quantile(0.25)
    Q3 = df[col].quantile(0.75)
    IQR = Q3 - Q1
    lower = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
    upper = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR
    df[col] = np.where(df[col] < lower, lower,
                       np.where(df[col] > upper, upper, df[col]))

# 5. Feature Engineering
# Basic engineered features
df["High_Discount"] = np.where(df["Discount_offered"] > df["Discount_offered"].median(), 1, 0)
df["Frequent_Buyer"] = np.where(df["Prior_purchases"] > df["Prior_purchases"].median(), 1, 0)
df["Weight_per_Cost"] = df["Weight_in_gms"] / (df["Cost_of_the_Product"] + 1)

# Advanced interactions
df["Weight_x_Cost"] = df["Weight_in_gms"] * df["Cost_of_the_Product"]
df["Discount_x_Prior"] = df["Discount_offered"] * df["Prior_purchases"]
df["Heavy_and_FrequentBuyer"] = np.where((df["Weight_in_gms"] > df["Weight_in_gms"].median()) & 
                                         (df["Prior_purchases"] > df["Prior_purchases"].median()), 1, 0)

# Binning numeric features
df["Cost_bin"] = pd.qcut(df["Cost_of_the_Product"], q=3, labels=[0,1,2])
df["Weight_bin"] = pd.qcut(df["Weight_in_gms"], q=3, labels=[0,1,2])
df["Prior_bin"] = pd.qcut(df["Prior_purchases"], q=3, labels=[0,1,2])

# 6. Encode Categorical Features
df = pd.get_dummies(df, drop_first=True)

# 7. Split Features & Target
X = df.drop(columns=[target])
y = df[target]

# 8. Handle Imbalanced Data (SMOTE)
smote = SMOTE(random_state=42)
X_resampled, y_resampled = smote.fit_resample(X, y)

# 9. Train-Test Split
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
    X_resampled, y_resampled, test_size=0.2, random_state=42, stratify=y_resampled
)

# 10. Scale Features
scaler = StandardScaler()
X_train = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)
X_test = scaler.transform(X_test)

# 11. Logistic Regression + Hyperparameter Tuning
param_grid = {
    "C": [0.01, 0.1, 1, 10],
    "penalty": ["l1", "l2"],
    "solver": ["liblinear", "saga"]
}

log_reg = LogisticRegression(max_iter=500, class_weight="balanced")
grid_search = GridSearchCV(log_reg, param_grid, cv=5, scoring="roc_auc")
grid_search.fit(X_train, y_train)

best_model = grid_search.best_estimator_

# 12. Predictions & Evaluation
y_pred = best_model.predict(X_test)
y_prob = best_model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]

accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
roc_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_prob)

print("✅ Best Parameters:", grid_search.best_params_)
print("✅ Accuracy:", accuracy)
print("✅ ROC-AUC:", roc_auc)
print("\nConfusion Matrix:\n", confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred))
print("\nClassification Report:\n", classification_report(y_test, y_pred))

# 13. ROC Curve
fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_test, y_prob)
plt.figure(figsize=(6, 5))
plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label="ROC Curve (AUC = %.2f)" % roc_auc)
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], "k--")
plt.xlabel("False Positive Rate")
plt.ylabel("True Positive Rate")
plt.title("ROC Curve - Logistic Regression")
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Import Libraries
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
import warnings;
warnings.filterwarnings('ignore');

# Load Dataset
df = pd.read_csv("Train.csv")
df.drop("ID", axis=1, inplace=True)  # Drop ID column
df.info()

# 1. Correlation Heatmap for Numerical Features
num_features = ['Customer_rating', 'Cost_of_the_Product', 'Discount_offered',
                'Weight_in_gms', 'Customer_care_calls', 'Prior_purchases']

corr_matrix = df[num_features].corr()
plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))
sns.heatmap(corr_matrix, annot=True, cmap='coolwarm', fmt=".2f")
plt.title('Correlation Heatmap of Numerical Features')
plt.show()

# 2. Pairplot for Numerical Features
sns.pairplot(df[num_features])
plt.suptitle('Pairwise Relationships Between Numerical Features', y=1.02)
plt.show()

# 3. Boxplots & Barplots for Numerical vs Categorical
plt.figure(figsize=(18, 14))

plt.subplot(3,3,1)
sns.boxplot(x="Mode_of_Shipment", y="Cost_of_the_Product", data=df)

plt.subplot(3,3,2)
sns.boxplot(x="Product_importance", y="Cost_of_the_Product", data=df)

plt.subplot(3,3,3)
sns.boxplot(x="Mode_of_Shipment", y="Discount_offered", data=df)

plt.subplot(3,3,4)
sns.boxplot(x="Warehouse_block", y="Weight_in_gms", data=df)

plt.subplot(3,3,5)
sns.barplot(x="Product_importance", y="Discount_offered", data=df)

plt.subplot(3,3,6)
sns.barplot(x="Mode_of_Shipment", y="Customer_rating", data=df)

plt.subplot(3,3,7)
sns.barplot(x="Warehouse_block", y="Discount_offered", data=df)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# 4. Countplots for Categorical Features
cat_features = ['Gender', 'Product_importance', 'Mode_of_Shipment', 'Warehouse_block']

for feature in cat_features:
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 4))
    sns.countplot(data=df, x=feature, palette='Set2')
    plt.title(f'Distribution of {feature}')
    plt.xlabel(feature)
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

# 5. Outlier Detection
for col in num_features:
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
    sns.boxplot(df[col])
    plt.title(f'Boxplot of {col}')
    plt.show()
